const flattened = matrix.reduce((acc, row) => acc.concat(row), []);
// [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]`,conceptContext:"An empty array initialized as the accumulator can be concatenated sequentially with nested rows inside a map closure.",description:"Now, let's learn how to flatten complex matrices without using the built-in `.flat()` array method.\n\nWrite a function `flattenGrid(grid)` that processes an array of nested arrays, merging them into a single 1D flat array using `.reduce()`.",codeTemplate:`function flattenGrid(grid) {
