const normal = userEmail.toLowerCase(); // "sarah.connor@skynet.com"`,conceptContext:"Using `.toLowerCase()` or `.toUpperCase()` normalizes input elements, securing lookup matching keys from erratic casing mismatches.",description:"Make user searches or credentials case-insensitive by normalizing text to lower or upper case!\n\nWrite a function `normalizeEmail(email)` that receives a string and returns a completely lowercased version of the email address.",codeTemplate:`function normalizeEmail(email) {
